<span class="lval" id="seq-bpm-val">90</span>
<label>Density</label>
<input id="seq-density" max="100" min="0" style="width:100px" type="range" value="70"/>
<span class="lval" id="seq-density-val">70%</span>
<button id="seq-play-btn">▶ PLAY</button>
<button class="gold" id="seq-evolve-btn">✦ EVOLVE</button>
<button id="seq-reset-btn">RESET</button>
</div>
<div class="edu-card">The probabilistic sequencer extends the classic 8-step pattern with stochastic firing: each step plays only if a random value falls below its probability threshold. This generates ever-varying rhythmic patterns from a fixed set of pitches — the core of generative melodic systems used by Brian Eno and contemporary modular synthesis.</div>
</section>
