<div class="edu-card">A Markov chain treats each musical state as a node in a probability graph. The matrix cell values define transition weights: a high probability at row C, column 3 means the system is likely to play C at time-step 3. In Markov mode, the current pitch biases the next pitch selection — the system composes itself forward.</div>
